# Shogi Web App

A modern Shogi (将棋) web application built with React and TypeScript. This project includes a responsive Shogi board, move history tracking, and a customizable UI using Tailwind CSS. Future improvements include AI integration, online multiplayer, and advanced rule enforcement.

## Features

* Interactive Shogi board with drag-and-drop functionality
* Move history tracking
* Game reset option
* Beautiful UI with Tailwind CSS
* Modular component structure for easy expansion

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

* Node.js (v18 or higher)
* npm or yarn

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/shogi-web-app.git
cd shogi-web-app
```

2. Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

3. Run the development server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

4. Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) in your browser.

## Project Structure

```
shogi-web-app/
├── src/
│   ├── App.tsx
│   ├── components/
│   │   ├── ShogiBoard.tsx
│   │   └── MoveHistory.tsx
│   └── styles/
│       └── main.css
├── public/
│   └── index.html
├── README.md
├── package.json
└── tsconfig.json
```

## Future Improvements

* AI integration (e.g., using Shogi engines like YaneuraOu)
* Online multiplayer mode
* Detailed rule enforcement (e.g., 二歩, 打ち歩詰め, 千日手)
* User profiles and ranking system
* Game analytics and move recommendations

